# 9. Project Code and Appeal Code creation

## Project Code

```m
#"Inserted Text Before Delimiter" = Table.AddColumn(#"Reordered Columns6", "Project Code", each Text.BeforeDelimiter([Gf_Apls_1_01_Ap_Appeal_category], " "), type text)
```

This takes the text before the first space from `Gf_Apls_1_01_Ap_Appeal_category`.

### Example

```text
"PRJ Community Appeals" → "PRJ"
```

This means the project code is being derived from the first token in the appeal category text.

### Risk

If appeal category formatting changes, this logic can break or return the wrong project code.

---

## Appeal Code

```m
#"Inserted Text Range" = Table.AddColumn(#"Inserted Text Before Delimiter", "Appeal Code", each Text.Middle([Gf_Apls_1_01_Appeal_ID], 2, 4), type text)
```

This extracts 4 characters starting at position 2 from the appeal ID.

### Example
If `Gf_Apls_1_01_Appeal_ID = "A123456"`
then `Appeal Code` becomes `1234`.

### Risk

This assumes a stable structure for the appeal ID.
If appeal IDs are not consistently formatted, the derived code may be wrong.

